'''''Son of Blagger''''', the sequel to ''[[Blagger (video game)|Blagger]]'', is a scrolling [[platform game]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/Personal_Computer_Games_Issue08/page/n31/mode/2up?view=theater|title=Personal Computer Games Issue08}}</ref> created by [[Antony Crowther|Tony Crowther]] and released by [[Alligata]] for the [[Commodore 64]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.the-commodore-zone.com/articlelive/articles/12/1/Tony-Crowther/Page1.html|title=Tony Crowther}}</ref> computer in 1983. A [[ZX Spectrum]] port by Elliot Gay<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.retrogamer.net/retro_games80/son-of-blagger/|title = Son of Blagger &#124; Retro Gamer| date=2 August 2009 }}</ref> and a [[BBC Micro]] port<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bbcmicro.co.uk/game.php?id=162|title = Son of Blagger}}</ref> were released in 1984.

==Legacy==
A clone of ''Son of Blagger'' was released for [[Amiga]], titled ''Jonas Fulstrand''. The game was released on a PD-Soft disk as ''Son of Blagger''.<ref>PD-Soft disk number 3162</ref>{{Better source|date=September 2019}}

